{{Unreferenced|date=November 2009}} {{Infobox hospital | Name = Georgetown Public Hospital | Org/Group = <!-- optional --> | Image = | image_size = | image alt = <!-- optional --> | Caption = | map_type = Guyana | map_caption = Shown in Georgetown, Guyana | Logo = <!-- optional --> | Logo Size = <!-- optional --> | Location = | Region = Georgetown, Guyana | Country = Guyana | Coordinates = {{coord|6.816405|-58.156482|display=inline,title}} | HealthCare = <!-- UK:NHS. AU/CA: Medicare. ELSE freetext, eg Private --> | Funding = Government | Type = General | Speciality = <!-- if devoted to a speciality (ie not a broad spectrum of specialities) and Type=Specialist/Teaching --> | Standards = <!-- optional if no national standards --> | Emergency = Yes | Affiliation = <!-- 'None' or Medical School and University affiliations (medical or paramedical) --> | Patron = <!-- 'None' or the individual who acts as the hospital patron --> | Network = <!-- optional --> | Beds = 600 | Founded = 1838 | Closed = <!-- optional --> | Website = <!-- 'None' or http URL --> | Wiki-Links = <!-- optional --> }} '''Georgetown Public Hospital''', in [[Georgetown, Guyana|Georgetown]], [[Guyana]], is the country's largest hospital. Its Seaman's Ward, the oldest section, was constructed in 1838. The hospital is government-run with a capacity of 600 beds, although not all are used due to staff shortages.
