This is a '''list of OECD countries by [[Unemployment#Long-term unemployment|long-term unemployment]] rate''' published by the [[OECD]]. This indicator refers to the number of persons who have been unemployed for one year or more as a percentage of the [[labour force]] (the sum of employed and unemployed persons). Unemployed persons are defined as those who are currently not working but are willing to do so and actively searching for work.
